            <h2>About the Harry Potter Universe</h2>
            <p>
                The Harry Potter universe is a fictional world created by J.K. Rowling. It centers around the adventures of the young wizard Harry Potter and his friends at Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry. The magical universe includes an elaborate system of magic, magical creatures, and richly developed characters, all intertwined with themes of friendship, bravery, and the fight against evil. The story spans seven books, which were later adapted into eight blockbuster movies.
            </p>
            <p>
                The universe also includes spin-off works such as "Fantastic Beasts," a series exploring the magical world before Harry's time. It features notable locations like Diagon Alley, Hogsmeade, and the Ministry of Magic, and iconic items such as the Elder Wand and the Marauder's Map.
            </p>
